text_Original:
back in the early 2000s, I was browsing IGN for new trailers of metal gear solid 2 at school. there was some kids next to me, who didnt know I spoke their native language talking shit because they saw an ad for buffy the vampire slayer on the IGN website and they interpreted it as an entire website based on that. 20+ years later, I work in IT and these people STILL exist.

I love this technology (I have first gen oculus and reverb g2) but when you include the mouth breathers of our society(the majority) + politicians, were going to be in a world of hurt, me thinks. Imagine the times when your family or friends showed/shared you a video they found online that was clearly faked but with a little dash of critical thinking, you  know its fake. Im mostly optimistic but with this quality, I have no faith in humanity and for once im pessimistic here. winter is coming guys. brace yourself.

text_Original:
People rightfully shit on Zuck. But this technology is going to be the strongest hedge we have against global nuclear hellfire. All the current global communication systems are too shallow in their information transfer and thus only allow for performative narcissism. This is the primary reason why twitter rose to be the most prominent medium of global communication. Being the shallowest one best allowed the narcissistic rent seekers to perform their puppet shows.  Full presence VR, as demonstrated, transfers a level of depth that is about as close as we can get to in person interaction. This depth of information transfer makes it extremely difficult for con artists and bots to hijack and take over things. Through increasing the depth of information transfer, we can achieve a much more human level of connection and interaction. 
I always point to the example of Daryl Davis, the black man who convinced over 200 KKK members to leave and renounce the organization. You could have confronted those people with all of the information of the most qualified and educated people, biologists, historians, philosophers, you name it. All that would have accomplished would have been to strengthen their conviction in the organization. But Daryl succeeded through the simple act of interacting at the human level, and in time becoming their friend. Full presence VR is the tech with the greatest potential to enable this interaction and connection at a global scale.

text_Original:
Hey hey hey - f&-k the idea of being able to alter the level at which you're able to emote. We know what Instagram filters and Photoshop have done to vulnerable people's self worth. You're talking about creating an unprecedented level of disparity between someone's reality and outward expression of themselves. If it's realism you're going for, stick to realism. Seriously, that's the biggest shittiest can of worms I've seen. Yes you're making space for 'expression' but with infinite unknown consequences. It must be blatantly clear in a meta interaction that you're communicating with someone who has chosen to alter the extent of their ability to emote. Like holy f"&k! You've talked about the importance of nuance, and in the same breath considered being able to alter it? 
I'm ready for a discussion and open to my viewpoint to be challenged, countered and explored üëä
